6. WWW CHANGED THE PLOT
---------------------------------

After the long term , Structural programming practices, Object Oriented Programming revolutionised the tech market.
C++ becomes highly efficient and less complex than C, accepting in all over working sectors even today. Even, due to
as fast as C, In Competitive Coding , C++ is first choice for programmers to go for. However, as C++ was enhanced
version of C, it still can uphold Structural Programming .

At the same time, the World Wide Web (WWW) idea came along and changed things again. As people started thinking about
programming for networks, they realized C++ had limitations. Slowly, C++ lacks Security, Robustness and the more
 important platform independence due to networks.
